title: Shares of several financial services companies are trading lower amid market weakness following US unemployment data and recent cautious comments from the WHO. Sentiment is also negative following cautious comments from Fed Chair Powell and bearish outlook from some major US investors on Wednesday. The financial sector has been impacted by lower business investment and spending as a result of the pandemic. Shares have reversed and are now trading higher.
